# 5. いつかの楽譜

Toya: This sheet music...
KAITO: I think it's for the piano.
KAITO: Wow, this looks hard. I don't think I have enough fingers for this.
KAITO: What's this song called? Let's see... The title says...
Toya: Fantaisie-Impromptu.
KAITO: Huh?
Toya: This is sheet music for Chopin's Fantaisie-Impromptu.
KAITO: What?! You can tell just by glancing at it?!
Toya: No, um... Another piece may not have been so obvious, but this one...
Toya: I practiced playing it so much when I was little.
KAITO: Oh...
KAITO: I see... Now I understand.
KAITO: That means... This sheet music might also have come from your feelings.
Toya: Yes. You're likely right.
Toya: (This really takes me back...)
Toya: (I remember spending every single day sitting at the piano.)
Toya: (Despite the fatigue, I had to keep my fingers moving... My vision even went blurry from time to time.)
Toya: (Things were so hard.)
Toya: (So hard that I found myself hating music itself.)
Toya: (But I'm able to keep moving forward today because of what I experienced back then.)
Toya: (That also applies to the task Ken gave me.)
Toya: My task... That's it, KAITO!
KAITO: Yes?
Toya: About the task you helped me the other day with... I think I know what I need to do now.
Toya: I should be able to produce some results now, so I hope you'll be looking forward to that.
KAITO: If you're willing to say that, Toya, then I think there's nothing for me to worry about!
KAITO: However, it is a bit unfortunate...
Toya: Huh? What is?
KAITO: How you've got such a good head on your shoulders!
Toya: ... Um...
Toya: Why is it unfortunate that I have a good head on my shoulders?
KAITO: Because I don't have anything to do now!
Toya: ...?
KAITO: I was hoping to help you all since you've been working so hard on your tasks, but it seems that I don't have anything to teach you, Toya...
KAITO: Once again, you found the solution all on your own!
Toya: I...see...
KAITO: In other words, I wish you'd lean on me more since I'm here in the first place to help you make your dreams a reality!
Toya: You've already helped me so much, KAITO.
KAITO: What...?! I... I have?
Toya: Yes.
Toya: Whether it's making me laugh whenever something is bothering me, or inviting me to have a nice meal with you and MEIKO...
Toya: Your kindness has always allowed me to take a step back and relax...and given me a chance to think about how to tackle my problems.
Toya: So, KAITO, thank you for everything you've done for me.
KAITO: Haha! Wow, now I'm the one receiving all the encouragement!
KAITO: Still, I'm glad to hear that I've been able to help you.
Toya: You have. And I'll be asking you for more help in the future.
KAITO: Excellent!
KAITO: I'll do everything I can to make sure you're all able to go beyond that giant wall!
Toya: Thank you. With that in mind...
Toya: I promise to surpass RAD WEEKEND! And—
KAITO: Hm? Did you hear that sound?
Toya: Yes, it seemed like it came from over by the wall...
Toya: ...! KAITO, there's a crack in it...!
KAITO: What?! Wow, and a fairly big one too!
KAITO: But why now...?
Toya: (This wall... It must have something to do with how we see RAD WEEKEND in our minds...)
Toya: Ah... Maybe that's it...
KAITO: Huh?
Toya: This is just my hunch...
Toya: But I think our desire to overcome the obstacle in front of us—to see what's beyond—is what caused this crack to form in the wall.
KAITO: Yes, I see...! So when you do find a way to overcome it, then maybe it'll crumble to pieces!
Toya: Hehe. You may be right. In any case...
Toya: I want to see what's beyond it as soon as I can.
